# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the LogicFlow project following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Package**: `@vercel/analytics@^2.0.1`
- **Method**: Installed via npm
- **Location**: Added to dependencies in `package.json`

### 2. Analytics Initialization File
- **Created**: `js/analytics.js`
- **Purpose**: Initializes Vercel Web Analytics using the `inject()` method
- **Implementation**: ES module that imports and calls the inject function from @vercel/analytics

### 3. HTML Files Updated
Added analytics script tag to all 10 HTML pages:
- `index.html` - Landing page
- `menu.html` - Main menu/dashboard
- `login.html` - Login page
- `registro.html` - Registration page
- `juego.html` - 3D simulator game
- `calculadora.html` - PSU calculator tool
- `glosario.html` - Technical glossary
- `retos.html` - Challenges page
- `actualizar-password.html` - Update password page
- `recuperar-password.html` - Password recovery page

Each page now includes:
```html
<script type="module" src="js/analytics.js"></script>
```

### 4. Build Verification
- ✅ Vite build completed successfully
- ✅ Analytics package properly bundled in output
- ✅ No build errors introduced
- ✅ All module imports resolved correctly

## Implementation Details

### Framework Detection
This is a vanilla JavaScript/HTML project using:
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Build Tool**: Vite 8.0.16
- **Module System**: ES Modules (type="module")

### Analytics Setup Method
Based on the official Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart and https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/package), I used:
- The `inject()` function from `@vercel/analytics`
- ES module imports (compatible with Vite bundler)
- Script tag with `type="module"` attribute for proper module loading

### Deployment Requirements
To activate analytics after deployment to Vercel:
1. Navigate to your Vercel project dashboard
2. Go to the Analytics tab
3. Click "Enable" to activate Web Analytics
4. Vercel will automatically add routes at `/_vercel/insights/*`
5. Analytics data will begin collecting on the next deployment

## Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with analytics package tree
- `js/analytics.js` - Created analytics initialization file
- All 10 HTML files - Added analytics script tag

## Notes
- Analytics will only be active when deployed to Vercel (not in local development)
- No configuration options were added - using default analytics behavior
- The implementation is non-invasive and preserves all existing functionality
- Script is loaded as a module before other page scripts to ensure early initialization
